Vintage-style illustration of a frustrated craftsman in a cluttered workshop, wielding an absurdly oversized sledgehammer while attempting to fix a delicate pocket watch mechanism on a workbench. The watch's intricate gears and springs are scattered everywhere, some crushed and bent. Behind him, a wall displays progressively larger hammers hanging on hooks. The scene is rendered in warm sepia tones with cross-hatching details, evoking early 20th century technical drawings. Dust motes float in shafts of light from a grimy window, and the craftsman's rolled-up sleeves and furrowed brow convey determined obliviousness to the absurdity of his approach.
